b'' b'configuration of ide harddisks' b'==============================' b'' b'' b'last update:\t14.4.1993' b'' b'and published regularly on comp.sys.ibm.pc.hardware.' b'' b'' b'!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!' b'there is explicitly no warranty' b'that the given settings are correct or harmless. (i only collect, i do' b'not check for myself!!!). there is always the possibility that the' b'settings may destroy your hardware!' b'!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!' b'' b'' b'since i hope however that only well-minded people undergo the effort of' b'posting their settings the chance of applicability exists. if you should' b'agree or disagree with some setting, let me know immediately in order' b'to update the list.' b'' b'if you possess a hd not mentioned here of which you know bios and/or' b'jumper settings, please mail them to me for the next update of the list!' b'' b'only ide (at-bus) harddisks will be accounted for.' b'if not specified the landing zone should be set equal to the number of' b"cylinders. if not specified the 'write precompensation' should be set" b"65535. (there are bioses that don't even ask for it)." b'' b'another statement (maybe right):' b"ide harddisk don't have precomp and lzone. the precomp is a built-in parameter" b"and lzone isn't used because most if not every ide disk has autopark." b'' b"the jumpers' names are given as printed on the hd's board, often only a" b"jumper number (jp12 means the jumper a zero means that the jumper" b'is left open, a one means that the jumper is closed.' b'' b'' b'' b'*************************** c o n n e r b'' b'' b'conner peripherals drive geometry' b'' b'ide/at' b'' b'conner drives are low level formatted at the factory. it is only necessary' b'to run setup, fdisk, and dos format.' b'' b'model heads cylinders sectors pcomp l-zone type table led' b'' b'cp2034 *ut n/a' b'cp2064 *ut n/a' b'cp2084 *ut n/a' b'cp3184 *ut a' b'cp3104 *ut a' b'cp3111 *ut a(?)' b'cp3204 *ut b' b'cp30064 *ut b' b'cp30084 *ut b' b'cp30104 *ut b' b'cp30084e *ut c' b'cp30174e *ut c' b'cp30204 *ut c' b'cp3304 *ut d' b'cp3364 *ut d' b'cp3504 *ut d' b'cp3554 *ut b' b'' b'table table b'' b'jumper settings jumper settings' b'' b'single drive jumper act and c/d single drive jumper c/d' b'master drive jumper act, c/d and dsp master drive jumper c/d dsp' b'slave drive no jumpers installed slave drive no jumpers installed' b'' b'' b'table b'all conner mbyte drives use' b'jumper settings drive type all conner b'mbyte drives use drive type b'single master drive jumper c/d' b'slave drive no jumpers installed *ut universal translate.' b'select a drive type that is' b'close to but does not exceed' b'the megabyte capacity of the' b'drive. the drive will' b'translate to the megabyte' b'capacity that you have' b'selected.' b'' b'led' b'' b'a: b: c: d:' b'j-4 j-5 j-5 j-3' b'pin pin pin pin b'pin pin pin pin b'' b'' b' when i installed a conner cp3204f mb) as master and a wd caviar b' mb) as slave, both with and without the "cp" jumper, the caviar had' b' seemingly normal behaviour. however, when doing writes to the caviar, once' b' in a while it would overwrite directories etc. using fastback was almost' b' impossible.' b'' b' the workaround is to install the caviar as the master, and the conner' b' as the slave.' b'' b'' b'' b'*************************** f u j i t s u b'' b'details of fujitsu drives m261xt (standard)' b'' b'm2614et m2613et m2612et m2611t' b'' b'heads (physical) b'cyl (physical) b'sec/trk b'speed (rpm) b'capacity 180mb 135mb 90mb 45mb' b'' b'' b'+-----------------------------------------------+' b'| b'+--+ b'psu cnh-2 b'+--+ b'1 led b'| cnh-1 cnh-3 connector b'| o o b'40-way b'ide b'| b'| b'+--+ b'+-----------------------------------------------+' b'' b'' b'' b'pin function' b'position' b'' b'* active mode' b'2- slave present mode' b'4- pin 27=iochrdy' b'cnh-1 jumpers pin 27=reserved' b'7- drive system' b'* drive system' b'10-11 pin 29=irq14 pin 31=reserved' b'* pin 31=irq14 pin 29=reserved' b'' b'' b'pin function' b'position' b'' b'1- slave drive mode' b'cnh-2 jumpers master drive mode' b'7- ecc bytes' b'* ecc bytes' b'' b'' b'pin function' b'position' b'' b'1- write protect enabled' b'cnh-3 jumpers write protect disabled' b'4- reserved' b'' b'key: (i guess!) marks factory default setting for jumper' b'' b'' b'bios settings' b'' b'bios setting for the m2614et in my system is cylinders, sectors' b'and heads.' b'' b' i was trying to set my ide drive in the subject above to a slave drive for' b' a conner 170mb drive and contacting the support company gave me this answer (which works). the factory default on sw2 is on off off off off off this sets the drive to be a single drive. setting sw2 to off on on off off off makes it a slave drive. sw1 has been set to on off off on all along.' b'' b'' b'' b'model cylinders heads sectors capacity (million bytes)' b'' b'm2622t b'm2623t b'm2624t b'' b'' b'there are switches on the switch block on these drives. only of' b'them have a use that i am aware of (from my m2624t manual):' b'' b'master/slave master sw1-5 off' b'slave sw1-5 on' b'ecc bytes bytes sw1-4 off' b'7 bytes sw1-4 on' b'write protect disabled sw1-3 off' b'enabled sw1-3 on' b'io channel ready disabled sw1-1 off' b'enabled sw1-1 on' b'' b'i have no idea about the function of sw1-2 and sw1-6. the values' b'listed with a are the factory default settings.' b'' b'' b'*************************** k a l o k b'' b'kalok\tkl3100\t mb' b'bios:\tcyl heads 6\tsectors b'' b'kalok kl3120 mb' b'bios:\t cyl heads sectors b'' b'the following jumper settings have been reported for kl3100 but are probably' b'also valid for other kalok drives.' b'' b'single hd:' b'o o o o o' b'' b'o o o o-o same row as pin of the ide connector.' b'' b'master (disk b'o o o o o' b'|' b'o o o o o' b'' b'slave:' b'o o o o o' b'|' b'o o o o o' b'' b'these pairs of pins are at the righthand side of the disk.' b'' b'' b'' b'*************************** m a x t o r b'' b'model cyls heads sectors precomp landing zone' b'----------\t-----\t-----\t-------\t-------\t------------' b'lxt-200a\t816\t15\t32\t0\t816' b'lxt-213a\t683\t16\t38\t0\t683' b'lxt-340a\t654\t16\t63\t0\t654' b'lxt437a\t\t842\t16\t63\t0\t842' b'lxt535a\t\t1036\t16\t63\t0\t1024' b'' b'jumpers are as follows:' b'' b'the bottom of the drive looks like this (well, sort of):' b'' b'| o o b'| o o b'| o o b'| o o b'| o o b'| b'+[power] [ide connector]-----+' b'' b'single drive\t dual drive system' b'pin numbers\tjumper\t\tsystem\t\tmaster\t\tslave' b'-----------\t------\t\t------------\t------\t\t-----' b'1-2\t\tslave drive\tremove\t\tremove\t\tinstall' b'3-4\t\tactivity led\toptional\toptional\toptional' b'5-6\t\tslave present\tremove\t\tremove\t\toptional' b'7-8\t\tmaster drive\tremove\t\tinstall\t\tremove' b'9-10\t\tsync spindle\tremove (n/a)\toptional*\tremove' b'' b'* only one drive (the master) in an array should have this jumper installed.' b'' b'' b'' b'maxtor 7060a j14 closed, j13 closed' b'maxtor 7060a j14 open, j13 open' b'maxtor 7060a j14 closed, j13 open' b'maxtor 7060a j14 open, j13 closed' b'' b'maxtor 7120a j14 closed, j13 closed' b'maxtor 7120a j14 open, j13 open' b'maxtor 7120a j14 closed, j13 open' b'maxtor 7120a j14 open, j13 closed' b'maxtor 7120a j14' b'' b'jumpers for the above drives:' b'' b'j11 i/o-channel ready open: disabled; close: enabled b'j13 see above' b'j14 see above' b'j15 operation-status open: normal; close: factory b'j j j j j' b'2 b'0 b'' b'power data-cable' b'' b'j16: idle mode latch open: disabled; close: enabled b'j17: drive model open: 7060a; close 7120a b'j18: ecc bytes open: bytes; close: bytes b'' b'master/slave: drive is master and alone j20 closed, j19 closed' b'drive is master of two drives: j20 closed, j19 open' b'drive is slave of two drives j20 open j19 closed' b'' b'' b'maxtor 7213a' b'' b'default (power-up) at bios translation parameters (others possible)' b'cyl hds spt mbytes' b'683 b'' b'there are two sets of jumpers. a set of and a set of' b'4. with the power and ide connector toward you, the set of is' b'numbered (left to right) j16 j20 and the set of is numbered' b'(bottom to top) j22-j25.' b'' b'the only jumper of normal interest is j20. jumper it for only' b'drive in a single drive system, or master drive in a dual drive' b'system.' b'' b'remove the jumper j20 for slave drive in a dual drive system.' b'' b'j19 is a dummy and may be used to store the spare shunt if the' b'drive is configured for a slave mode.' b'' b'jumpers j17, j18, j24, j25 are factory reserved. abnormal operation' b'may occur if jumpered.' b'' b'jumper is sync spindle enabled/disabled (open=disabled)' b'jumper is sync slave/master (open=slave)' b'jumper is i/o channel ready (open=disabled)' b'' b'' b'maxtor 7245a (245mb ide; self-parking; universal translate):' b'drive type user defineable' b'cyl hds wpc lz s/t' b'967 (wpc and lz optional)' b'' b'master(2): j20 closed' b'slave(2): j20 open (use j19 for shunt storage)' b'single: j20 closed' b'' b'' b'********************** m i c r o p o l i s b'' b'' b'drive\t\t2105a\t\t2112a' b'----------------------------------------' b'unformatted mb\t647\t\t1220' b'formatted mb\t560\t\t1050' b'platters\t5\t\t8' b'heads\t\t8\t\t15' b'cylinders\t1760\t\t1760' b'----------------------------------------' b'' b'performance (both):' b'' b'track to track (read)\t\t1.5 msec' b'track to track (write)\t\t2.5 msec' b'average\t\t\t\t10 msec' b'max\t\t\t\t25 msec' b'avg rotational latency\t\t5.56 msec' b'rotational speed\t\t5400 rpm b'data transfer rate\t\tupto 5mbytes/sec' b'internal data rate\t\t24-40 mbits/sec' b'' b'bios settings:' b'' b'2105a\t\t1084 cyl\t16 heads\t63 sectors' b'2112a*\tmaster\t1024 cyl\t16 heads\t63 sectors' b'slave\t1010 cyl\t16 heads\t63 sectors' b'' b'* the 2112a emulates both master and slave' b'' b'' b'jumpers (labelled j6 on the drive)' b'' b'----' b'|oo| w1\\ only these are used' b'|oo| w2/' b'|oo|' b'|oo|' b'|oo|' b'--