lave' b'1 master in pdiag mode using sp to check if slave present' b'1 master in 40/80a mode using sp to check if slave present' b'1 single drive' b'' b'=======================================================' b'' b'lps at jumpers' b'ds sp dm* meaning' b'0 slave in standard pdiag mode for compatibility with drives that use' b'pdiag-line to handle master/slave communications' b'0 slave in prodrive 40/80a mode compat. without using pdiag line' b'0 self test' b'0 self test' b'1 master in pdiag mode using dasp to check for slave' b'1 master in 40/80a mode using dasp to check for slave' b'1 master in pdiag mode using sp to check for slave without' b'checking dasp' b'1 master in 40/80a mode using sp to check for slave without' b'checking dasp' b'' b'' b'======================================================================' b'* while my spec form marked the jumper name dm, it is labeled as cs on' b'my lps 240at drive.' b'' b'' b'' b'the quantum els series:' b'' b'model cap avg acc cylinders heads sectors/track' b'(mb) (ms)' b'' b'els42at b'els85at b'els127at b'els170at b'' b'write precomp for all quantum drives probably no significance)' b'landing zone cylinders' b'' b'straps: if an els drive is' b'master only, use ds' b'master with slave, ds or, ds and sp in some cases' b'slave, no strap' b'' b'' b'*************************** r o d i m e b'' b'information for ro 3008a and ro 3009a series hard disk drives:' b'' b'drive types' b'' b'model\tcyls\thds\tsectors/trk\t no. blocks\tformatted cap.' b'-------\t----\t---\t-----------\t ----------\t--------------' b'ro3058a\t868\t 3\t 34\t\t 88,536\t mbyets' b'ro3088a\t868\t 5\t 34\t\t 147,560\t mbyets' b'ro3095a\t923\t 5\t 34\t\t 156,910\t mbyets' b'ro3128a\t868\t 7\t 34\t\t 206,584\t105.77 mbyets' b'ro3135a\t923\t 7\t 34\t\t 219,674\t112.47 mbyets' b'' b'ro3059a\t217\t15\t 28\t\t 91,158\t mbyets' b'ro3089a\t325\t15\t 28\t\t 136,737\t mbyets' b'ro3129a\t492\t15\t 28\t\t 206,645\t105.80 mbyets' b'ro3139a\t523\t15\t 28\t\t 219,735\t112.50 mbyets' b'ro3209a\t759\t15\t 28\t\t 319,053\t163.35 mbyets' b'ro3259a\t976\t15\t 28\t\t 410,211\t210.02 mbyets' b'' b'' b'link options' b'' b'in order to install the rodime ro 3000a series drives the dumpers for' b'the single/dual drive and led operation on the drive need to be set as' b'described in the relevant product specification.' b'i a single drive environment the drive is described as a master.' b'in a dual drive environment the drives are described as a master and a' b'slave. this is due to the protocal the takes place between the two drives' b'when performing diagnostics.' b'there are four links, lk1, lk2, lk4 and lk5, adjacent to the way' b'interface connector. they have the following functions and are described' b'in order as viewed from the end of the drive, with the first jumper' b'described nearest the way interface connector.' b'' b'lk2: led' b'when fitted, this jumper connects the led drive to pin of the' b'interface. this allows a led to be connected to the interface. an' b'external current limiting resistor needs to be fitted in series with' b'the led when this option is selected. the value of the resistor will' b'be dependant on the led type chosen but will be in the range of b'ohms ot ohms.' b'' b'lk1: dual drives' b'this jumper must be fitted when two drives are attached to a single' b'bus. it fallows communication across the way interface connector,' b'indicating, to the master drive, the presence of a slave.' b'' b'lk4: master' b'when fitted this signifies that the drive jumpered is a master. if' b'there are two drives connected on a single bus then only one may be' b'jumpered in this way.' b'' b'lk5: iochrdy' b'when fitted this connects the iochrdy signal to the drive, it is' b'fitted when the drive is used in host systems that have a higher' b'data transfer rate than the drive i.e. greater than mbytes per' b'second when using interleave. this jumper is not normally' b'fitted as most hosts transfer at a lower rate than mbytes per' b'second.' b'' b'there are four possible master/slave configurations in which a drive(s)' b'may be jumpered:' b'' b'master, single drive with led on interface\t\tlk2 lk4 fitted.' b'master, single drive without led on interface\tlk4 only fitted.' b'master, dual drive without led on interface\tlk4 lk1 fitted.' b'slave, dual drive without led on interface\t\tno jumpers fitted.' b'master, dual drive with led on interface\t\tlk4, lk1 lk2 fitted.' b'slave, dual drive with led on interface\t\tlk2 only fitted.' b'' b'the master drive will delay power-up for approximately two seconds to' b'reduce power surges in applications where dual drives are used.' b'' b'the other connections for a led will be found close to the way' b'connector at the other end of the drive. this led driver is not affected' b'by the link options. an internal current limiting resistor is on the' b'drive for this led driver. refer to the product specification for further' b'details.' b'' b'' b'' b'' b'*************************** s e a g a t e b'' b'there is a list of most seagate hd (including mfm, scsi, esdiand ide) on' b'every simtel mirror under' b'' b'/msdos/dskutl/1seagate.zip' b'' b'it contains info about the following drives:' b'' b'st1144a\tst138a\t st274a\tst3283a' b'st1057a st1156a\tst1400a st280a\tst351ax' b'st1090a st1162a\tst1401a st3051a\tst9051a' b'st1102a st1186a\tst1480a st3096a\tst9077a' b'st1111a st1201a\tst157a\t st3120a\tst9096a' b'st1126a st1239a\tst2274a st3144a\tst9144a' b'st1133a st125a\tst2383a st325ax' b'' b'' b'*********************\tt e a c b'' b'model: sd-3105' b'' b'cyls. heads sect/t precmp lzone capacity' b'------ b'physical b'bios (ami) (100.2m)' b'(award) (99.9m)' b'(phoenix) (100.0m)' b'' b'connectors and jumpers:' b'' b'+----+ jumper function' b'|....| on: -act selected (ext.led)' b'| off: -slv present selected' b"+----+ on: two hdd's" b'j2 j7 j1 off: single hdd' b'power (power) signal jumpers on: master (/single)' b'off: slave (with units used)' b'3 on: -i/o ch rdy not o